# Tesco PLC — Corporate Valuation Model (DCF + Trading Comps)

## Overview
A full corporate valuation of Tesco PLC (LSE: TSCO) built in Excel, 
covering a 3-year DCF and European peer trading comparables analysis.

## What's inside
- **Assumptions** — All model drivers in one place (colour-coded inputs)
- **Income Statement** — FY2022A–FY2025A actuals + FY2026E–FY2028E projections
- **DCF Valuation** — WACC (6.5%), UFCF, Gordon Growth terminal value, sensitivity table
- **Trading Comps** — EV/EBITDA & P/E across 6 European peers
- **Football Field** — Blended valuation summary with analyst conclusion

## Key Findings
- DCF base case implies ~£3.60–3.80 vs. market price of £3.42 (fairly valued)
- Terminal value drives ~70–75% of EV — TGR and WACC are the key assumptions
- Net Debt/EBITDA of 2.0x (FY2025A), Baa3/BBB– investment-grade credit rating
- IFRS 16 note: reported net debt of £9.5bn includes ~£8–9bn lease liabilities

## Data Sources
- Tesco PLC Annual Reports FY2022–FY2024
- Tesco PLC Preliminary Results FY2025 (April 2025)
- Tesco Investor Relations (tescoplc.com)
- Analyst consensus estimates: Stockanalysis.com

